720923f-b.title: Manhattan: Lexington Avenue - 23rd Street (East)
720923f-b.text:
Lexington Ave. (foreground) at the S.E. corner of East 23rd Street (left) showing the old College of the City of New York under demolition. A modern school building was erected here later to replace same. On the left appears several structures on the north side of East 23rd Street, between Lexington and Third Aves. The spire appearing on the right is of the Swedish Lutheran Churdh on East 22nd Street. This set consists of
a negative and a positive.
February 7, 1928.
Robert A. Knudsten.
Gift of Albert A. Volk Co.
